{"ts":"2026-06-26T22:48:44.850Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Addressing Data Persistence**\n\nOkay, I've got a key point to resolve: the assessment page isn't retaining user progress. I need to implement a local workspace to ensure data persists. The requirements explicitly call for this feature. I'm focusing on how best to integrate this local workspace for a seamless user experience.\n\n\n**Designing Workspace Continuity**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on a design for persistent data! The goal is a user-centric \"Local Sandbox Workspace\". I'm planning a `workspaceUtility.ts` file with state-saving utilities to persist work across sessions. This will be the \"Sovereign Client Edge Vault\" experience, preserving user actions like ROI adjustments, DAG configurations, simulations, and assessments locally within their browser for a Premium experience.\n\n\n**Implementing Continuity Features**\n\nI'm now thinking about UI implementation for the workspace! I need to ensure a clear and user-friendly experience for the local data persistence. A \"Local Storage\" indicator banner or panel seems key to emphasize the in-browser saving. A `workspaceUtility.ts` will provide the save/load utilities for tool states. I'll add an interactive workspace preview block in `/build/page.tsx`, displaying tools with data, statuses, and resume/reset actions. This will also show a secure banner regarding data encryption and local storage. There should also be a global \"Reset Workspace\" button.\n\n\n**Refining Persistence Strategy**\n\nI'm now refining the persistence strategy for individual tool pages! I'm planning a premium status bar or panel—perhaps \"⚡ Saved to Local Workspace\"—for each tool, with an option to reset. Auto-saving is the plan, either on every state change (with debouncing) or upon form completion. I'll guard browser APIs with `typeof window !== 'undefined'` and a `mounted` state to prevent SSR hydration mismatches. Mobile responsiveness is also key for the workspace preview. I plan to change `workspaceUtility.ts`, `app/build/page.tsx`, and individual tool pages for this functionality.\n\n\n**Excluding Irrelevant Files**\n\nI'm now determining which files to modify for this feature. I've confirmed I should avoid the landing page files, checking the `/app/build/` pages to ensure this. I've begun creating `components/build/workspaceUtility.ts`, to contain the utility. I'm working on defining a `WorkspaceState` interface to structure the saved data, including blueprints, assessments, and ROI data.\n\n\n**Structuring Workspace Data**\n\nI'm now figuring out how to structure all saved data. I've defined interfaces to structure the saved data including `proposal`, `talk`, `sandbox`, and `marketplace` data. I'm focusing on their key fields such as company details, search queries, and selected filters.\n\n\n"}}
