{"ts":"2026-06-26T22:49:20.217Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Designing Local Workspace Utility**\n\nI'm now diving into the design of a local workspace utility. I plan to build a custom `components/build/workspaceUtility.ts` file. This should address the need for local storage persistence, as the pages currently lack this. I'm focusing on how the pages currently manage their state to inform the utility's design.\n\n\n**Defining Workspace State Types**\n\nI'm solidifying the data structure within `workspaceUtility.ts`. I'm establishing standard types for different workspace states and considering helper functions for saving, loading, and clearing those states, including potential keys to write. The design leans toward using a unified key, `gff_local_workspace`, but I am also considering `gff_proposal_draft_intake` and `gff_blueprint_history` keys for specific data isolation. I'm focusing on type safety, hydration guards, and error handling.\n\n\n**Fetching Existing Blueprint Data**\n\nI'm now reading from `gff_proposal_draft_intake` and `gff_blueprint_history` to display items in the overview panel. I believe I can unify these different storage points into a unified \"Local Workspace\" listing. I'm focusing on the `/build` page's tools and the existing contents of `components/build/`, which include `types.ts`, `components.tsx`, `index.ts`, `services.ts`, and `WizardStepperSystem.tsx`, to find a perfect place for my changes. I think the `workspaceUtility.ts` file is a perfect fit to start fetching existing blueprints in LocalStorage via `gff_blueprint_history`.\n\n\n\n**Reviewing Stored Blueprint Data**\n\nI've examined the saved data structures. The \"assessment,\" \"roi,\" \"proposal,\" and \"talk\" blueprints seem key. I can now display the count of stored blueprints from the `gff_blueprint_history` key, as well as their basic data. I'm noting the data includes things like scores, industries, intake input structures, and last updated times.\n\n\n**Enumerating Utility Tool States**\n\nI'm now identifying the different state structures across the application. I've categorized states for the Blueprint, Assessment, ROI, Proposal, Talk to Agent, Sandbox, Marketplace, and Foundry Studio tools. I'm focusing on the state keys: `selectedIndustry`, `selectedFunction`, `selectedAgentType`, `searchQuery`, `activeAgentId`, `lastUpdated` for each tool, and documenting specific marketplace and foundry studio key-value pairs. My goal is to organize these states for persistence. I am now writing `components/build/workspaceUtility.ts` file to export helper functions.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T22:49:20.220Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"ctcg4b0y","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/components/build/workspaceUtility.ts","new_text":"\"use client\";\n\nimport { Industry, CompanySize, Priority } from \"./types\";\n\n// State types for each of the 8 Build tools\n\nexport interface AssessmentWorkspaceState {\n  answers: Record<string, number>;\n  activeDimensionIndex: number;\n  showResult: boolean;\n  lastUpdated?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ROIWorkspaceState {\n  industry: string;\n  companySize: string;\n  opFunction: string;\n  annualCostBaseline: number;\n  processVolume: number;\n  avgHandlingTime: number | \"\";\n  automationTarget: number;\n  manualEffort: string;\n  productivityImprovement: number;\n  implementationHorizon: string;\n  initialInvestment: number;\n  priority: string;\n  lastUpdated?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ProposalWorkspaceState {\n  companyName: string;\n  industry: string;\n  companySize: string;\n  primaryChallenge: string;\n  customChallenge: string;\n  priorityOutcomes: string[];\n  targetTimeline: string;\n  preferredEngagementPath: string;\n  budgetRange: string;\n  geography: string;\n  stakeholders: string;\n  lastUpdated?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface TalkWorkspaceState {\n  currentStep: number;\n  data: {\n    companyName: string;\n    industry: string;\n    primaryChallenge: string;\n    targetSystem: string;\n    securityClearance: string;\n    estimatedUsers: string;\n    urgency: string;\n    email: string;\n  };\n  showResults: boolean;\n  lastUpdated?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface SandboxWorkspaceState {\n  selectedIndustry: string;\n  selectedFunction: string;\n  selectedAgentType: string;\n  searchQuery: string;\n  activeAgentId: string;\n  lastUpdated?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface MarketplaceWorkspaceState {\n  activeTab: string;\n  industryFilter: string;\n  functionFilter: string;\n  maturityFilter: string;\n  platformFilter: string;\n  searchQuery: string;\n  compareIds: string[];\n  lastUpdated?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface FoundryStudioWorkspaceState {\n  selectedPresetId: string;\n  selectedPattern: string;\n  stages: any[];\n  knowledgeSources: string[];\n  lastUpdated?: string;\n}\n\n// Master Local Workspace Interface\nexport interface GFFWorkspace {\n  assessment?: AssessmentWorkspaceState;\n  roi?: ROIWorkspaceState;\n  proposal?: ProposalWorkspaceState;\n  talk?: TalkWorkspaceState;\n  sandbox?: SandboxWorkspaceState;\n  marketplace?: MarketplaceWorkspaceState;\n  foundryStudio?: FoundryStudioWorkspaceState;\n}\n\nconst WORKSPACE_KEY = \"gff_local_workspace_continuity\";\nconst BLUEPRINT_KEY = \"gff_blueprint_history\";\nconst PROPOSAL_KEY = \"gff_proposal_draft_intake\";\n\n// Safe JSON parser/serializer wrappers\nconst isBrowser = typeof window !== \"undefined\";\n\nexport function getFullWorkspace(): GFFWorkspace {\n  if (!isBrowser) return {};\n  try {\n    const raw = localStorage.getItem(WORKSPACE_KEY);\n    if (raw) {\n      return JSON.parse(raw) as GFFWorkspace;\n    }\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(\"Error reading full GFF local workspace:\", err);\n  }\n  return {};\n}\n\nexport function saveFullWorkspace(workspace: GFFWorkspace) {\n  if (!isBrowser) return;\n  try {\n    localStorage.setItem(WORKSPACE_KEY, JSON.stringify(workspace));\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(\"Error saving full GFF local workspace:\", err);\n  }\n}\n\n// Get/Set for Assessment\nexport function getAssessmentState(): AssessmentWorkspaceState | undefined {\n  return getFullWorkspace().assessment;\n}\n\nexport function saveAssessmentState(state: Omit<AssessmentWorkspaceState, \"lastUpdated\">) {\n  const ws = getFullWorkspace();\n  ws.assessment = {\n    ...state,\n    lastUpdated: new Date().toISOString()\n  };\n  saveFullWorkspace(ws);\n}\n\n// Get/Set for ROI\nexport function getROIState(): ROIWorkspaceState | undefined {\n  return getFullWorkspace().roi;\n}\n\nexport function saveROIState(state: Omit<ROIWorkspaceState, \"lastUpdated\">) {\n  const ws = getFullWorkspace();\n  ws.roi = {\n    ...state,\n    lastUpdated: new Date().toISOString()\n  };\n  saveFullWorkspace(ws);\n}\n\n// Get/Set for Proposal (also syncs with legacy key for backward compatibility)\nexport function getProposalState(): ProposalWorkspaceState | undefined {\n  if (!isBrowser) return undefined;\n  // Try newer consolidated first\n  const consolidated = getFullWorkspace().proposal;\n  if (consolidated) return consolidated;\n\n  // Fallback to older direct key\n  try {\n    const rawLegacy = localStorage.getItem(PROPOSAL_KEY);\n    if (rawLegacy) {\n      return JSON.parse(rawLegacy) as ProposalWorkspaceState;\n    }\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(\"Error reading legacy proposal draft:\", err);\n  }\n  return undefined;\n}\n\nexport function saveProposalState(state: Omit<ProposalWorkspaceState, \"lastUpdated\">) {\n  const ws = getFullWorkspace();\n  const updated = {\n    ...state,\n    lastUpdated: new Date().toISOString()\n  };\n  ws.proposal = updated;\n  saveFullWorkspace(ws);\n\n  // Sync with legacy key\n  if (isBrowser) {\n    try {\n      localStorage.setItem(PROPOSAL_KEY, JSON.stringify(state));\n    } catch (err) {\n      console.error(\"Error syncing legacy proposal draft:\", err);\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n// Get/Set for Talk To Agent\nexport function getTalkState(): TalkWorkspaceState | undefined {\n  return getFullWorkspace().talk;\n}\n\nexport function saveTalkState(state: Omit<TalkWorkspaceState, \"lastUpdated\">) {\n  const ws = getFullWorkspace();\n  ws.talk = {\n    ...state,\n    lastUpdated: new Date().toISOString()\n  };\n  saveFullWorkspace(ws);\n}\n\n// Get/Set for Sandbox\nexport function getSandboxState(): SandboxWorkspaceState | undefined {\n  return getFullWorkspace().sandbox;\n}\n\nexport function saveSandboxState(state: Omit<SandboxWorkspaceState, \"lastUpdated\">) {\n  const ws = getFullWorkspace();\n  ws.sandbox = {\n    ...state,\n    lastUpdated: new Date().toISOString()\n  };\n  saveFullWorkspace(ws);\n}\n\n// Get/Set for Marketplace\nexport function getMarketplaceState(): MarketplaceWorkspaceState | undefined {\n  return getFullWorkspace().marketplace;\n}\n\nexport function saveMarketplaceState(state: Omit<MarketplaceWorkspaceState, \"lastUpdated\">) {\n  const ws = getFullWorkspace();\n  ws.marketplace = {\n    ...state,\n    lastUpdated: new Date().toISOString()\n  };\n  saveFullWorkspace(ws);\n}\n\n// Get/Set for Foundry Studio\nexport function getFoundryStudioState(): FoundryStudioWorkspaceState | undefined {\n  return getFullWorkspace().foundryStudio;\n}\n\nexport function saveFoundryStudioState(state: Omit<FoundryStudioWorkspaceState, \"lastUpdated\">) {\n  const ws = getFullWorkspace();\n  ws.foundryStudio = {\n    ...state,\n    lastUpdated: new Date().toISOString()\n  };\n  saveFullWorkspace(ws);\n}\n\n// Get Blueprints saved count or history list from BLUEPRINT_KEY\nexport interface BlueprintHistoryItem {\n  id: string;\n  timestamp: string;\n  data: any;\n  score: number;\n  category: string;\n}\n\nexport function getBlueprintHistory(): BlueprintHistoryItem[] {\n  if (!isBrowser) return [];\n  try {\n    const raw = localStorage.getItem(BLUEPRINT_KEY);\n    if (raw) {\n      return JSON.parse(raw) as BlueprintHistoryItem[];\n    }\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(\"Error reading blueprint history:\", err);\n  }\n  return [];\n}\n\n// Clear single tools\nexport function clearToolState(tool: keyof GFFWorkspace | \"blueprint\") {\n  if (!isBrowser) return;\n  if (tool === \"blueprint\") {\n    try {\n      localStorage.removeItem(BLUEPRINT_KEY);\n    } catch (err) {\n      console.error(\"Error resetting blueprint history:\", err);\n    }\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const ws = getFullWorkspace();\n  delete ws[tool];\n  saveFullWorkspace(ws);\n\n  if (tool === \"proposal\") {\n    try {\n      localStorage.removeItem(PROPOSAL_KEY);\n    } catch (err) {\n      console.error(\"Error resetting proposal legacy key:\", err);\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n// Complete Workspace Reset\nexport function purgeAllWorkspace() {\n  if (!isBrowser) return;\n  try {\n    localStorage.removeItem(WORKSPACE_KEY);\n    localStorage.removeItem(BLUEPRINT_KEY);\n    localStorage.removeItem(PROPOSAL_KEY);\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(\"Error purging all local workspaces:\", err);\n  }\n}\n\n// Check if any workspace exists\nexport function hasAnyWorkspace(): boolean {\n  if (!isBrowser) return false;\n  const ws = getFullWorkspace();\n  const hasConsolidated = Object.keys(ws).length > 0;\n  if (hasConsolidated) return true;\n\n  // Check legacy blueprint/proposal\n  const bps = getBlueprintHistory();\n  if (bps.length > 0) return true;\n\n  const prop = localStorage.getItem(PROPOSAL_KEY);\n  if (prop) return true;\n\n  return false;\n}\n"}}}
