ing Persistence Strategy**\n\nI've just confirmed the straightforward approach to auto-saving tool states. On component mount, I'll load the state using `getToolState(\"assessment\")`. Any change to `answers`, `activeDimensionIndex`, or `showResult` will trigger a save using `saveToolState(\"assessment\", { answers, activeDimensionIndex, showResult })`. The simplicity of this approach is quite satisfying, which is encouraging!\n\n\n**Refining Auto-Reset**\n\nI've got the auto-reset working in `assessment/page.tsx` now. The `handleReset` function clears the tool state via `clearToolState(\"assessment\")`, ensuring a clean slate. I've integrated `getToolState`, `saveToolState`, and `clearToolState` from `@/components/build/workspaceUtility` as well. This is a very elegant solution!\n\n\n"}}
